OL,3,CEnergy bills expected to rise by #146
OL,4,Cahead of winter months
OL,6,FBills could be about to rise by nine-
OL,7,Fpercent, our Consumer Editor Chris
OL,8,FChoi has the details.
OL,10,FThe average household energy bill is
OL,11,Fset to rise by #146 in October when
OL,12,Fthe latest change to the price cap
OL,13,Ftakes effect, according to experts.
OL,15,FEnergy consultancy Cornwall Insight
OL,16,Fsaid it expects the typical
OL,17,Fhousehold's energy bill to increase by
OL,18,F9% to #1,714 a year, up from #1,568
OL,19,Fcurrently, on October 1.
