OL,6,FThe energy price cap was introduced by
OL,7,Fthe government in January 2019 and
OL,8,Fsets a maximum price that energy
OL,9,Fsuppliers can charge consumers in
OL,10,FEngland, Scotland and Wales for each
OL,11,Fkilowatt hour (kWh) of energy they use.
OL,13,FThe price cap does not limit a
OL,14,Fhousehold's total bills because people
OL,15,Fstill pay for each unit of gas and
OL,16,Felectricity they use - the figures
OL,17,Fprovided are calculated for an average-
OL,18,Fuse household and if more energy than
OL,19,Faverage is used, a household will pay
OL,20,Fabove the cap.
